WEBVTT

00:04.671 --> 00:07.215
♪ We are The Fungies ♪

00:07.298 --> 00:10.593
♪ Prehistoric fungi
in a mushroom to-own ♪

00:10.677 --> 00:12.011
♪ Outside we look different ♪

00:12.095 --> 00:13.638
♪ Inside we're the same ♪
Yeah!

00:13.722 --> 00:15.932
♪ Everyone's a Fungie
in their own way ♪

00:16.015 --> 00:18.268
♪ Come join The Fungies ♪

00:18.351 --> 00:21.521
♪ Explore a brand-new world
made just for yo-ou ♪

00:21.604 --> 00:23.356
♪ If you're inclusive,
inquisitive ♪

00:23.440 --> 00:24.899
♪ Respectful, and kind ♪

00:24.983 --> 00:28.361
♪ You can be a Fungie, too ♪

00:28.862 --> 00:34.784
♪♪

00:34.868 --> 00:38.413
Seth: Okay, let's see what mom's
got on the old grocery list.

00:38.496 --> 00:40.749
Shale, slate, granite.

00:40.832 --> 00:43.460
Sounds about time
for a trip to...

00:43.543 --> 00:46.421
the Miner's Market!

00:47.255 --> 00:50.467
Fast carts to your right,
slow carts to your left.

00:50.550 --> 00:52.886
Come on, hurry up!

00:52.969 --> 00:54.596
Holk, wait up!

00:54.679 --> 00:56.890
I'm shopping
for my mom today!

00:56.973 --> 00:58.308
Very responsible.

00:58.391 --> 01:00.769
Hey, why are you
in the slow lane?

01:00.852 --> 01:04.814
My dads won't let me
ride the fast carts.

01:04.898 --> 01:06.107
Aaah!

01:06.191 --> 01:08.568
[ Screaming ]

01:08.651 --> 01:11.529
Oh, my mom just kind of
lets me do whatever.

01:13.656 --> 01:15.825
I need to ride
those carts, Seth.

01:15.909 --> 01:18.870
That's why
I made this.

01:18.953 --> 01:21.915
To show
I'm responsible.

01:21.998 --> 01:24.667
Is that a box of rocks
arranged by...

01:24.751 --> 01:26.044
the Mohs scale?

01:26.127 --> 01:28.922
All these rocks are arranged
from softest to hardest.

01:29.005 --> 01:34.219
Talc is a soft 1, and a diamond
is the hardest at 10!

01:34.302 --> 01:37.180
Oh, who are these
handsome Fungies?

01:37.263 --> 01:38.890
Those are my dads.

01:38.973 --> 01:43.228
I want to be great miners
like them someday.

01:43.311 --> 01:46.022
It<i> was</i> too fast.

01:46.105 --> 01:48.525
Got to ride
those carts.

01:54.113 --> 01:55.406
Hey, Dads!

01:55.490 --> 01:57.158
Hey, Holk!

01:57.242 --> 01:58.743
This is my friend Seth.

01:58.827 --> 02:01.704
Hogan, this is the kid
always wreaking havoc

02:01.788 --> 02:03.456
around Fungietown.

02:03.540 --> 02:04.541
Wow.

02:04.624 --> 02:06.000
My mom lets me
do whatever.

02:06.084 --> 02:07.752
How do you
like the setup?

02:07.836 --> 02:09.546
Holk: Dad, look!

02:09.629 --> 02:13.216
Think this proves I know
enough to ride the fast carts?

02:13.299 --> 02:16.636
What? No, those carts
are way too fast!

02:16.719 --> 02:18.513
Well, I feel better.

02:18.596 --> 02:22.600
[ Screaming ]

02:22.684 --> 02:23.726
[ Clattering ]

02:23.810 --> 02:25.311
Okay, new plan.

02:25.395 --> 02:27.105
What if I run the table?

02:27.188 --> 02:29.691
I'll sell everything.

02:29.774 --> 02:32.318
-Sell everything?!
-Sell everything?!

02:32.402 --> 02:34.445
Even the black opals?

02:36.573 --> 02:39.492
They're so expensive,
they never sell.

02:39.576 --> 02:41.452
Oh, I'll sell them.

02:41.536 --> 02:45.248
And if I do,
you let me ride the fast carts.

02:45.331 --> 02:46.958
Oooooh.

02:47.041 --> 02:48.585
This might actually work.
Let's let him.

02:48.668 --> 02:53.173
Okay, Holk, if you can sell
everything, it's a deal.

02:53.256 --> 02:55.675
Yes!

02:56.426 --> 02:59.387
And we can finally
catch a movie.

02:59.470 --> 03:01.764
Good luck!
Holk! Holk! Holk! Holk!

03:01.848 --> 03:03.099
Oh, dang, Holk,

03:03.182 --> 03:07.020
this whole market
is yours for the taking.

03:07.103 --> 03:10.523
Yeah, I can do this.
Bleh.

03:10.607 --> 03:12.108
I'll make you proud.

03:12.191 --> 03:14.694
You know your minerals
like the back of your hand.

03:14.777 --> 03:16.321
Who wouldn't want to buy
from you?

03:16.404 --> 03:21.075
Me! I wouldn't purchase
a single pebble from you.

03:21.159 --> 03:24.162
Oh, great.
It's Dranger.

03:24.245 --> 03:26.289
Go back to your booth!

03:26.372 --> 03:27.624
Or what?

03:27.707 --> 03:30.001
You'll get in a fast cart
and get your dads?

03:30.084 --> 03:33.421
Oh, yeah.
You're not allowed.

03:33.504 --> 03:34.756
Smell you later.

03:34.839 --> 03:37.342
[ Laughs ]

03:37.425 --> 03:38.343
[ Hisses ]

03:38.426 --> 03:40.970
Uh, do you
know that guy?

03:41.054 --> 03:42.263
Dranger.

03:42.347 --> 03:45.975
Dranger hates anyone
who's happier than him.

03:46.059 --> 03:47.560
Which is everyone!

03:47.644 --> 03:51.147
Some people say it's because
his skin is so itchy.

03:51.230 --> 03:52.815
[ Roars ]

03:53.650 --> 03:55.985
Well, I wouldn't worry
because you're about to make

03:56.069 --> 03:59.072
your first sale
to this guy.

03:59.155 --> 04:02.659
Um, would you recommend
a good family entrée?

04:02.742 --> 04:05.078
Oh, first sale,
don't mess up.

04:05.161 --> 04:06.162
Okay.

04:06.245 --> 04:07.497
[ Mumbling ]

04:07.580 --> 04:10.291
Uh, how about some feldspar?

04:10.375 --> 04:12.794
Crunchy, filling,
and affordable.

04:12.877 --> 04:14.837
Sold. To me.

04:14.921 --> 04:16.839
Whoop.
You're a natural.

04:16.923 --> 04:19.717
Thanks, Holk.
I'm doing it.

04:19.801 --> 04:23.262
[ Humming ]

04:24.263 --> 04:26.557
♪ Shopping for my mom ♪

04:26.641 --> 04:29.310
♪ Shopping for my mom
but also for me ♪

04:29.394 --> 04:31.604
Rock Candy.
Rock Candy.

04:31.688 --> 04:32.814
Candy Rocks here.

04:32.897 --> 04:34.941
Candy Rocks.
Rock, rock, rock.

04:35.024 --> 04:36.025
Rock, rock, rock.

04:36.109 --> 04:38.778
Well, got to
finish mom's list.

04:38.861 --> 04:40.196
Hmm.

04:40.279 --> 04:42.865
Vendor:
Free topaz samples!

04:42.949 --> 04:45.076
Free topaz samples here.

04:45.159 --> 04:46.327
Oh. Thank you.

04:46.411 --> 04:48.746
What an effective
marketing strategy.

04:48.830 --> 04:51.040
Hey, kid!

04:51.124 --> 04:53.293
Aw, that's nice, Pooger.

04:53.376 --> 04:55.128
I made 'em
all myself.

04:55.211 --> 04:58.423
Oh, Pooger.
This is incredible.

04:58.506 --> 05:00.591
[ Clang ]
"Live, Laugh, Mine."

05:00.675 --> 05:02.760
[ Clang ]
"I'd Rather Be Mining."

05:02.844 --> 05:04.721
[ Clang ]
"Mine Over Matter"?

05:04.804 --> 05:10.143
They provide inspiration
in harrowing times of need.

05:13.771 --> 05:15.940
Okay, what do I have left?

05:16.024 --> 05:17.817
Oh, just some quartz.

05:17.900 --> 05:19.277
A-ha.

05:19.360 --> 05:20.903
[ Humming ]

05:20.987 --> 05:22.697
Huh? Dranger!

05:22.780 --> 05:25.324
I'm trying to
get groceries here.

05:27.035 --> 05:28.911
[ Muttering ]

05:28.995 --> 05:30.747
[ Laughs ]

05:30.830 --> 05:34.000
[ Sighs ] That guy stinks.

05:34.083 --> 05:36.586
9 and 10.

05:36.669 --> 05:38.546
Thank you
for your purchase!

05:38.629 --> 05:41.466
I'm really doing it,
aren't I?

05:41.549 --> 05:43.092
[ Crying ]
Please stop.

05:43.176 --> 05:46.012
Please stop crying.
Please be quiet.

05:48.306 --> 05:50.433
That ruby looks
a little hard.

05:50.516 --> 05:53.853
May I interest you
in some soft calcite?

05:53.936 --> 05:56.105
[ Crying ]

05:56.189 --> 05:57.398
[ Cooing ]

05:57.482 --> 06:00.735
[ Gasps ]
I'll take all you have!

06:00.818 --> 06:03.237
[ Cash register dings ]

06:03.321 --> 06:05.281
Hmm. Boop.

06:05.364 --> 06:06.407
What's this?

06:06.491 --> 06:07.825
Oh, it's a free
sample sign.

06:07.909 --> 06:09.952
Trust me, it could
help business.

06:10.036 --> 06:11.621
That's a good idea,

06:11.704 --> 06:15.541
but I don't know
if I'll be needing it.

06:15.625 --> 06:16.834
My stars.

06:16.918 --> 06:20.963
This calls for a celebratory
pickaxe key chain.

06:21.047 --> 06:22.381
Thanks, Seth.

06:22.465 --> 06:24.675
I still got to sell those
black opals, though.

06:24.759 --> 06:25.885
No sweat.

06:25.968 --> 06:28.221
They'll be sold
before you can say...

06:28.304 --> 06:29.388
-Dranger!
-Dranger!

06:29.472 --> 06:31.307
You'd better
pay for those!

06:31.390 --> 06:34.894
I would if you weren't
giving them away...

06:34.977 --> 06:36.312
for free!

06:36.395 --> 06:37.396
[ Both gasp ]

06:37.480 --> 06:39.023
Curse you,
free sample sign.

06:39.107 --> 06:42.318
Now you'll never ride
those fast mine carts.

06:42.401 --> 06:43.778
[ Laughs ]

06:43.861 --> 06:46.197
Seth, we got to
get them back.

06:46.280 --> 06:47.698
[ Snoring ]

06:47.782 --> 06:50.159
Rock, rock, rock...

06:50.243 --> 06:52.286
Rock, rock, rock, rock, rock...

06:52.370 --> 06:53.287
There.

06:53.371 --> 06:55.248
Buy something or scram!

06:55.331 --> 06:58.876
Uh...guess
I'll try a sample.

06:58.960 --> 07:00.711
What?

07:00.795 --> 07:02.713
Nobody eats sand.

07:02.797 --> 07:04.465
That's why it's free.

07:04.549 --> 07:06.384
What a terrible salesman.

07:06.467 --> 07:08.678
Look. The opals.

07:08.761 --> 07:10.513
Follow me.

07:10.596 --> 07:12.598
Buy my stuff, you losers!

07:12.682 --> 07:14.142
[ Munching ]

07:14.225 --> 07:17.562
You kids?!
I'm not giving back my opals!

07:17.645 --> 07:20.648
Well, we just wanted to try some
of your free samples.

07:20.731 --> 07:23.734
[ Laughs ]
Help yourself.

07:23.818 --> 07:25.987
Don't mind if I do.

07:26.070 --> 07:27.446
Ahhhh.

07:27.530 --> 07:28.698
Psych!

07:28.781 --> 07:29.699
Aah!

07:29.782 --> 07:31.993
Quick, Holk,
grab the box.

07:32.076 --> 07:33.286
Ha!
Oh!

07:33.369 --> 07:35.830
Did you really think
sand would stop me?

07:35.913 --> 07:39.250
Well, it didn't.
'Cause I'm a super smart adult,

07:39.333 --> 07:42.211
and you're just
a couple of babies.

07:42.295 --> 07:43.296
Babies?!

07:43.379 --> 07:44.589
That's it.

07:44.672 --> 07:46.215
[ Cries ]

07:46.299 --> 07:47.967
Oh. I see.

07:48.050 --> 07:49.051
[ Crying ]

07:49.135 --> 07:52.847
The bad man
stole my opals!

07:52.930 --> 07:56.017
And he made me
drop my lolly!

07:56.100 --> 07:57.351
[ Crying ]

07:57.435 --> 07:59.604
[ Crying ]

07:59.687 --> 08:01.898
You did this
to children?!

08:01.981 --> 08:03.649
Yeah, but who hasn't?

08:03.733 --> 08:05.151
You monster!

08:05.234 --> 08:08.446
[ Groans ]

08:08.529 --> 08:09.864
Aah!

08:11.616 --> 08:13.242
[ Laughs ]

08:14.410 --> 08:16.078
He's headed for the carts!

08:16.162 --> 08:17.747
[ Laughing ]

08:17.830 --> 08:19.624
Whee!

08:19.707 --> 08:22.126
But, Holk,
you're not allowed.

08:22.210 --> 08:24.128
I've got to get
those opals back.

08:24.212 --> 08:27.089
You're a braver
Fungie than I.

08:27.173 --> 08:30.134
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

08:30.218 --> 08:32.428
[ Screaming ]

08:34.597 --> 08:37.683
Oh, yeah,
I love the slow carts.

08:39.018 --> 08:40.519
My dads were right!

08:40.603 --> 08:42.355
This<i> is</i> too fast!

08:44.232 --> 08:47.068
Get a grip, Holk.
We got to finish this thing.

08:47.151 --> 08:48.945
[ Laughing ]

08:49.028 --> 08:50.571
Whee!

08:50.655 --> 08:52.990
Looking for these?

08:53.074 --> 08:54.116
Duh!

08:54.200 --> 08:57.286
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

08:57.370 --> 08:59.622
I can't do this.

08:59.705 --> 09:00.790
Yes, you can.

09:00.873 --> 09:03.292
Mine over matter.

09:03.376 --> 09:04.377
You're right.

09:04.460 --> 09:05.419
Let's see.

09:05.503 --> 09:07.588
Rocks, rocks,
rocks, rocks...

09:07.672 --> 09:11.259
We're getting close
to the entrance, which means...

09:12.385 --> 09:13.261
[ Gasps ]

09:13.344 --> 09:14.720
Talc deposits!

09:14.804 --> 09:17.139
This mine is full of 'em.

09:17.223 --> 09:20.142
Talc is a 1 on the Mohs scale.

09:20.226 --> 09:23.187
It means it's soft.

09:26.065 --> 09:27.608
Missed me!

09:29.735 --> 09:31.570
[ Laughing ]

09:31.654 --> 09:33.698
[ Screams ]

09:35.366 --> 09:36.701
Yay!
Yes!

09:36.784 --> 09:39.996
Wait, we're gonna crash!

09:40.079 --> 09:41.664
Make it stop!

09:44.583 --> 09:46.210
Uh, what now?

09:46.294 --> 09:47.503
Uh, try this.

09:47.586 --> 09:49.505
It's a diamond,
it's a 10 on the --

09:49.588 --> 09:51.299
Yeah, I get it.

09:51.799 --> 09:53.801
[ Grunts ]

09:55.761 --> 09:57.179
Phew.

09:57.263 --> 09:58.764
[ Gasps ]

09:58.848 --> 10:00.641
The opals!

10:00.725 --> 10:02.476
Aah!

10:02.560 --> 10:05.354
[ Gasps ] My itching...

10:05.438 --> 10:06.689
it's gone.

10:06.772 --> 10:10.026
Oh, yeah, Talc helps
sooth irritated skin.

10:10.109 --> 10:11.652
I feel
so much better.

10:11.736 --> 10:14.363
Like I'm not mad
at the world anymore.

10:14.447 --> 10:15.698
Honk: Holk!

10:15.781 --> 10:19.285
Oh, my gosh, we told you to
stay off the fast carts!

10:19.368 --> 10:20.995
Please, this is my fault.

10:21.078 --> 10:23.914
Besides, your child
cured my maddening itchiness.

10:23.998 --> 10:27.752
Plus, Holk had the highest sales
in the whole market today.

10:27.835 --> 10:29.253
[ Sobbing ] I wanted
to sell all the...

10:29.337 --> 10:30.755
so I could ride the...

10:30.838 --> 10:33.758
but I had to get
the opals back, and I...

10:33.841 --> 10:36.344
Holk, we're just glad
you're okay.

10:36.427 --> 10:37.845
Seth: Yeah, it's a miracle.

10:37.928 --> 10:41.599
These fast mine carts
are really not up to code.

10:41.682 --> 10:45.770
Hey, to celebrate your sales,
why don't we try these?

10:45.853 --> 10:47.563
They never sell anyway.

10:47.646 --> 10:48.731
[ Munching ]

10:48.814 --> 10:50.441
-Mm.
-Mm.

10:50.524 --> 10:51.484
-Blech!
-Blech!

10:51.567 --> 10:53.069
-Yuck.
-Disgusting.

10:53.152 --> 10:54.570
Why did you make us
eat these?

10:54.653 --> 10:58.157
Just power through it.
They're a delicacy.

10:58.240 --> 10:59.283
Hmm.

10:59.367 --> 11:01.744
I kind of like 'em.
[ Laughs ]

11:01.827 --> 11:03.829
[ Laughter ]

11:03.913 --> 11:05.456
Seth: Classic Dranger.

11:05.539 --> 11:17.760
♪♪

11:17.843 --> 11:19.887
My mom lets me do whatever.
